            "name": "Tick",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Tick Diseases",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Giant ticks and tick swarms can potentially inflict diseases other than tick fever. Potential diseases that a tick could spread include blinding sickness, bubonic plague, malaria, or scarlet fever. The saving throw DC should be adjusted to DC 17 (for giant ticks) or DC 27 (for tick swarms).",
